--- In nbwrpg@yahoogroups.com, "airly2000" <airly2002@h...> wrote:
> Rodimus:
> 
> "Go ahead"said Rodimus, he left Nighlight's body in a lab table and 
> give her a kiss in her forehead, after that he moved to a side and 
> motioned Kenzo to start to work
> 
> 
Kenzo first went to work removing her weapons.  He had to use more
conventional tools because the advanced reassembly chamber was still
trashed.  Next he restrained her arms and legs with to the table with
steel cuffs.  Then he set up the energy field.  It was a lesser
version of the base energy shield.  He was a bit worried here, because
he wasn't sure if a vork could pass through it or not, though it
blocked other forms of energy such as laser beams and directed energy
weapons so theoretically it could prevent an energy being such as a
vork from passing through.  He injected her with an antidote to the
tranquilizer and rapidly switched on the energy field.  A blue glow
formed around the table. 

He waited silently for her to wake.
